The Songhua River is a tributary of the Heilong River (called Amur River in Russia) on the border between the Russian far east and China.HARBIN, Nov. 24 (Xinhua) The front of the polluted water of Songhua River in northeast China reached Harbin, capital of Heilongjiang Province, on early Thursday morning, local environment authority said.
China pledged on Thursday it will try its utmost to minimize the impact of northeast China's Songhua River pollution on the neighboring Russia, including intensifying monitoring and water quality control measures.
